Gorge of King Xorb to track down my old adversary: the Goblin Alchemist (see my earlier story, A day in the life of a monk, for my last encounter with the Alchemist).<br>
<br>
Perhaps Quellious was smiling on me, perhaps the celestial orbs were in the right configuration, and perhaps Clawfist, last Kerran monk of the Ashen Order, was watching me from beyond the grave but as I ran down the path toward Runnyeye I sensed the dice of destiny being rolled. And yes, just as I neared the entrance to Runnyeye Citadel, I spied the ugsome brute. He stood flanked by lesser goblin minions and surrounded by an eldritch glow as magical powers coursed through his body. I snuck past him and waited in the entrance to Runnyeye for my wounds to heal so that I might be assured of dealing death to the vile creature.<br>
<br>
While I waited my faithful friend Niffo, short of stature but big of heart and sole, learned that my vigil was at an end and raced to my side that we might combat the goblin together. <br>
<br>
And so the battle was joined. I flung my fists at the creature in a flurry of fury, while Niffo stood back and tried to stun the creature to prevent it accessing its magical powers. The tide of battle hung in the balance, as I was poisoned and then diseased by the alchemist, and then Niffo was assailed by the lesser creatures of the area who had risen to defend their champion. But slowly we wore down the defences of the alchemist until finally he turned to run and I knew that he was beaten. When he finally fell I sent forth my thanks to Quellious, and retrieved Clawfist's mace from the dank corpse of the alchemist.<br>
<br>
After the battle Niffo and I celebrated and drank some cleansing ale, and I thanked Niffo with all my heart for I fear that the battle would have been lost without his aid.<br>
<br>
But the other remains of Clawfist must still be gathered for his soul to be allowed to rest. Now I must seek out another goblin alchemist, rumoured to be seen in Misty Thicket, before I brave the depths of Runnyeye itself to conclude my search.<br>
<br>
Gumbrils<br>
